children.text: There are bends in the flexible ductwork that are too sharp, without adequate radius bends or support.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 4254 – Ductwork for air-handling systems in buildings, Part 1: Flexible duct, requires that
‘Flexible duct work shall be installed with a minimum bend radius to flexible duct diameter of 1 to 1. (See Figure 6)’ ;
These areas should be rectified to ensure they comply with the relevant Australian Standards, and to ensure efficiency in the ductwork system.
